      • RequestQueue

        public RequestQueue(ShopGun shopGun,
                    Cache cache,
                    Network network,
                    int poolSize,
                    Delivery delivery)
        Construct a new RequestQueue for processing requests. This RequestQueue is primarily aimed at fetching data from the ShopGun API.
        Parameters:
        shopGun, - the ShopGun SDK object to use for requests
        cache - to use for this RequestQueue
        network - the implementation you want to use for this RequestQueue
        poolSize, - number of threads to do requests
        delivery - object for returning objects to UI thread

      • finish

        public void finish(Request<?> request)
        This method is mostly for statistics and allows RequestQueue to tie up any loose ends that might be in a request. In the future, this can be used for better SDK cache control as multiple requests to the same endpoint, can be queued, and only one may be dispatched. On complete the others can be triggered, and instantly hitting local cache.
        Parameters:
        request - - request, that finished
